This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of mixture models, which are a type of probabilistic model commonly used in machine learning (ML) and statistics. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.NE (neural networks). Finally, the paper mentions the use of evaluation metrics and techniques for assessing the quality and diversity of generated translations, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CV (computer vision) that also deal with evaluation and performance metrics.
